PN,30601
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1777579557
OL,3,CRecommended use of some nasal sprays
OL,4,Climited to five days, regulator
OL,5,Cannounces
OL,7,FThe medicines regulator has changed
OL,8,Fguidance on decongestant nasal sprays,
OL,9,Fcapping recommended use of some
OL,10,Fproducts at five days.
OL,12,FIt follows two reports by ITV News
OL,13,Frevealing the scale of so-called nasal
OL,14,Fspray "addiction", with millions of
OL,15,Fpeople in the UK potentially having
OL,16,Fused the product long enough to put
OL,17,Fthemselves at risk.
OL,19,FThe MHRA also announced leaflets will
OL,20,Fcontain "strengthened" wording on the
OL,21,Frisks of prolonged use.
OL,26,@vD@GOUvD@QO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1777579557
OL,3,CRecommended use of some nasal sprays
OL,4,Climited to five days, regulator
OL,5,Cannounces
OL,7,FNasal sprays and drops containing
OL,8,Fxylometazoline and oxymetazoline can
OL,9,Frelieve congestion, but they are only
OL,10,Fmeant to be used on a short-term basis.
OL,12,FOverusing them may lead to a condition
OL,13,Fknown as rebound congestion, or
OL,14,Frhinitis medicamentosa.
OL,16,FSufferers experience chronic
OL,17,Fcongestion from repeatedly taking the
OL,18,Fmedication, which they feel can only
OL,19,Fbe relieved by using more of the
OL,20,Fproduct.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1777579557
OL,3,CRecommended use of some nasal sprays
OL,4,Climited to five days, regulator
OL,5,Cannounces
OL,7,FRebound congestion can also cause
OL,8,Fdamage to tissues inside the nose,
OL,9,Faccording to the MHRA.
OL,11,FThe change will see all new packaging
OL,12,Fand leaflets for the products stating
OL,13,Fthe five-day limit on use, changed
OL,14,Ffrom the previous limit of seven days.
OL,16,FIn a press release on April 30, the
OL,17,FMHRA said it had taken the step "in
OL,18,Fline with advice from Expert Advisory
OL,19,FGroups to the Commission on Human
OL,20,FMedicines due to adverse effects
OL,21,Ffollowing prolonged use".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1777579557
OL,3,CRecommended use of some nasal sprays
OL,4,Climited to five days, regulator
OL,5,Cannounces
OL,7,FIn January, research by Ipsos and ITV
OL,8,FNews revealed more than a fifth of
OL,9,Fadults who have used these products
OL,10,Fhave done so for longer than seven
OL,11,Fdays.
OL,13,FThis means an estimated 5.5 million
OL,14,Fpeople in the UK could have risked
OL,15,Fdeveloping a dependency to nasal
OL,16,Fsprays containing xylometazoline and
OL,17,Foxymetazoline.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1777579557
OL,3,CRecommended use of some nasal sprays
OL,4,Climited to five days, regulator
OL,5,Cannounces
OL,7,FFollowing our first report into the
OL,8,Fissue, ITV News received thousands of
OL,9,Fcomments and emails from those who had
OL,10,Fsuffered the effects of rebound
OL,11,Fcongestion - some, for decades.
OL,13,FWe heard reports of problems with
OL,14,Fsleep, anxiety, intense congestion and
OL,15,Fheadaches when attempting to stop
OL,16,Fusing these types of nasal sprays.
OL,18,FIn rare cases, some even undergo
OL,19,Fsurgery to alleviate the effects.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1777579557
OL,3,CRecommended use of some nasal sprays
OL,4,Climited to five days, regulator
OL,5,Cannounces
OL,7,FThao Huynh, Head of Respiratory
OL,8,FImaging and Critical Care at the MHRA,
OL,9,Fsaid: "If your nose is still blocked
OL,10,Fafter five days of using a nasal
OL,11,Fspray, it could be caused by overuse
OL,12,Fof the product, rather than your
OL,13,Foriginal symptoms.
OL,15,F"Continuing to use it could make the
OL,16,Fproblem worse. Instead, talk to a
OL,17,Fhealthcare professional about stopping
OL,18,Fuse of the product and whether
OL,19,Falternative treatments could help.
OL,26,@qD@GOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
